<div class="container">
    
    <div class="header">
        <h1>🌳 Acorn City Kids</h1>
        <div class="subtitle">☀️ Summer 2026 Ultimate Guide</div>
        <p class="intro">Connecting Wake County families to free, affordable, and fully inclusive activities focused on kindness, nature, and community.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section-title"><span>✨</span> Featured June Events</div>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Cars and Carnivores Street Festival:</strong> A vibrant, free community street fair featuring a massive display of cars, local food, and family-friendly activities. 
            <span class="event-date">📅 Saturday, June 6, 2026 — Downtown Wake Forest</span>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Blueberry Bash:</strong> A fun, produce-themed farmers market morning packed with kids' activities, interactive trivia, and family entertainment.
            <span class="event-date">📅 Saturday, June 20, 2026 — Western Wake Farmers' Market</span>
        </li>
    </ul>

    <div class="section-title"><span>🎨</span> Free & Low-Cost Workshops</div>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Native Voices, Cultures, and Art Making:</strong> A wonderful, completely free family day featuring hands-on art projects, traditional games, storytelling, and live cultural performances.
            <span class="event-date">📅 Saturday, June 6, 2026 — Gregg Museum of Art & Design</span>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Wake County Library Summer Reading Challenge:</strong> Pop into any Wake County Public Library location all summer long to pick up free reading logs, track books, and claim fun prize incentives!
            <span class="event-date">📅 Running All Summer — All Wake County Library Branches</span>
        </li>
    </ul>

    <div class="section-title"><span>🌳</span> Nature & Animals</div>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Dueling Dinosaurs Sensory-Friendly Morning:</strong> A quieter, calmer, limited-crowd opportunity to explore the incredible dinosaur exhibits with reduced noise stimuli. Fidget toys and noise-reducing headphones are available.
            <span class="event-date">📅 Sunday, June 14, 2026 — NC Museum of Natural Sciences</span>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Wetland & Greenway Explorers:</strong> Pack a picnic and explore the completely free paved paths, wildlife viewing platforms, and shaded trails at Lake Johnson Park or the Neuse River Trail.
            <span class="event-date">📅 Open Daily — Free Public Access</span>
        </li>
    </ul>

    <div class="section-title"><span>♿</span> Special Needs & Inclusive Programs</div>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Marbles Kids Museum Sensory Friendly Playtime:</strong> A specialized, highly supportive environment designed exclusively for children with disabilities and their families to explore the museum at a relaxed pace with lower lighting and minimal noise.
            <span class="event-date">📅 Wednesday, June 17, 2026 (Repeats Monthly through August) — Downtown Raleigh</span>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Sensory-Friendly Play at Urban Air:</strong> An exclusive morning session customized for children on the autism spectrum and with sensory needs. Enjoy the active parks safely with no loud music or intense flashes.
            <span class="event-date">📅 Saturday, June 20, 2026 — Urban Air Raleigh</span>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Sensory Storytime:</strong> An interactive, welcoming literacy program explicitly structured for autistic children and those with neurodivergent sensory needs.
            <span class="event-date">📅 Saturday, June 27, 2026 — North Regional Library</span>
        </li>
    </ul>

